I don&#x27;t know about that link, but in general you would use a fix point combinator. The Fit library has a fix point combinator here:<p><a href="http://pfultz2.github.io/Fit/doc/html/fix/" rel="nofollow">http://pfultz2.github.io/Fit/doc/html/fix/</a><p>So you could implement a generic factorial like this:<p><pre><code>    auto factorial = fit::fix([](auto self, auto x) -> decltype(x) 
    { 
        return x == 0 ? 1 : x * self(x-1); 
    });</code></pre>
